Class TwoThreeFourTreeInt

java.lang.Object
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.tree.twothreefourtree.AbstractTwoThreeFourTreeInt
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.tree.twothreefourtree.TwoThreeFourTreeInt
All Implemented Interfaces:
BaseOpsInt, TreeOpsInt
public class TwoThreeFourTreeInt extends AbstractTwoThreeFourTreeInt

Title: TwoThreeFourTree

Description:

Int implementation for a 234 tree which allows the user to create instances of trees with integer values. The 234 tree has three different types of nodes, which the tree is named after, which can hold that number + 1 connections as children nodes. It uses splitting in order to keep is access time minimal. Note that a 234 tree is a self-balancing tree which checks the colors of the nodes in the subtrees to ensure equal distancing of nodes and minimal search time
Version:
1.0
Author:
Sam R. Thangiah
